    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="870"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1896</hi>
                        </date>. (Received July 30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 919.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the Rev. Mr.
                    Baird, a missionary educator, has gone to Bitlis to supply the place of the Rev.
                    George Knapp. In pursuance of the agreement with me by the Turkish Government
                    that when a missionary was withdrawn another should take his place, every
                    facility was afforded to Mr. Baird by traveling teskereh, etc., by the
                    Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
